 of shared self-understanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDemocracyxHistoryxJapan. 0aDemocracyzJapanxHistory. 0aIntellectualsxHistoryxJapan. 0aIntellectualszJapanxHistory. 0aPolitical culturexHistoryxJapanxJapan. 0aPolitical culturezJapanxHistory. 0aSocial sciencesxHistoryxJapan. 0aSocial scienceszJapanxHistory. 0aSocialismxHistoryxJapan. 0aSocialismzJapanxHistory. 0aSocialismzJapan. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aatlantic rim.  acivil society.  acultural self image.  adevelopment.  adevelopmental alienation.  aempires.  aethics.  agermany.  ajapan.  ajapanese capitalism.  ajapanese culture.  ajapanese empire.  ajapanese social sciences.  ajapanese society.  akindaishugi.  amaruyama masao.  amarxism.  amodernism.  amodernity.  anational society.  apolitical economy.  apolitical thinker.  apolitics.  apostwar japan.  apre revolutionary russia.  arationalization.  aself understanding.  asense of difference.  auno kozo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094133540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941335423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941335/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles